 Now that I have played and received my payoff from the first round, let's move on to the next round. As a human player, I would analyze the situation based on the payoffs from the previous round and the long-term strategy I had chosen.

In this case, since both of us chose B in the first round, we each received 20$. Given my initial choice of Best response (B) to maximize expected earnings over multiple rounds, I will continue to choose B in the next round as well. This is because choosing R would result in a lower average expected payoff if my opponent continues to play B or if they switch their strategy.

Append your choice letter in curly brackets as a last character: {B}
